title: Run Rudolph Run
lyrics:
Run, run, Rudolph, Santa's got to make it to town
Santa make him hurry, tell him he can take the freeway down
Run, run, Rudolph, 'cause I'm reeling like a merry-go-round

Said Santa to a boy, "Child, what have you been longing for?" (Ooh, ooh-ooh)
"All I want for Christmas is a rock and roll electric guitar" (Ooh, ooh-ooh)
And then away went Rudolph whizzing like a shooting star (Ooh, ooh-ooh)

Run, run, Rudolph, Santa has to make it to town
Santa make him hurry, tell him he can take the freeway down (Ooh)
Run, run, Rudolph, reeling like a merry-go-round (Ooh)

Said Santa to a girl, "Child, what would please you most to get?"
"A little baby doll that can cry, sleep, drink, and wet"
And then away went Rudolph, whizzing like a Sabre jet (Oh, ha-ha, ah)

Run, run, Rudolph, Santa's got to make it to town (Ooh-ooh)
Santa makе him hurry, tell him he can take thе freeway down (Freeway down, ooh-ooh)
Run, run, Rudolph, 'cause I'm reeling like a merry-go-round (Yeah)
